---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="DonjonSec Privacy Policy for the Donjon Platform. Learn what data we collect, what we do not collect, and how your data is used."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-navy-950 py-16 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg text-slate-400">
          Last updated: February 2026
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Privacy Content -->
  <section class="bg-navy-900 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="space-y-12">

        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            This Privacy Policy describes how DonjonSec ("we," "us," "our") collects, uses, and handles information in connection with the Donjon Platform software ("Software") and the donjonsec.com website ("Website"). This policy applies to all editions of the Software: Community, Pro, Enterprise, and MSSP.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- What We Collect -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">1. What We Collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            The Software may collect and transmit the following data to DonjonSec servers for the purposes described in this policy:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">License Activation Data</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; License key status, activation timestamps, and edition tier information used for license validation and compliance.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Version Information</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Software version, build number, and update status to ensure you are running the latest version and to deliver relevant updates.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Usage Statistics</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Aggregate, anonymized statistics on which features and scanners are used and how frequently. No specific scan data is included.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Error and Crash Reports</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Crash reports, error codes, and stack traces to help us diagnose and fix bugs. These reports do not contain personal data or assessment content.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">System Configuration</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Operating system type and version, available memory, and processor type to help us optimize the Software for your environment.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- What We Do NOT Collect -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">2. What We Do NOT Collect</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            The Donjon Platform is designed with data privacy as a core principle. The Software does NOT intentionally collect or transmit:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Assessment Content, Targets, or Results</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; The content, targets, or results of any assessments or scans you perform.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Network Information of Assessed Systems</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; IP addresses, hostnames, or network topology of systems you assess.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Credentials and Personally Identifiable Information</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Customer data, passwords, API keys, tokens, certificates, names, email addresses, or any other personal data.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-red-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Assessment Findings and Remediation Details</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Vulnerability data, compliance gaps, risk scores, remediation recommendations, or any assessment output.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-500">
            In the event of unintentional collection of data described above, DonjonSec will promptly delete such data upon discovery or upon written notification by the customer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Telemetry Controls by Edition -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">3. Telemetry Controls by Edition</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            Telemetry controls vary by license tier. We are transparent about what each edition collects and the controls available to you.
          </p>
          <div class="mt-6 overflow-x-auto">
            <table class="w-full text-left text-sm" role="table">
              <caption class="sr-only">Telemetry controls by software edition</caption>
              <thead>
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-700">
                  <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Edition</th>
                  <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Telemetry Status</th>
                  <th scope="col" class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-400 font-medium">Can Disable?</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-slate-300">
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-800">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Community</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Enabled by default</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-slate-500">No &mdash; cannot be disabled</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-800">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Pro</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Enabled by default</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-cyan-400">Yes, via configuration</td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-b border-navy-800">
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">Enterprise</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Enabled by default</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-cyan-400">Yes; Zero Data Retention available</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium">MSSP</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3">Customer-controlled</td>
                  <td class="px-4 py-3 text-cyan-400">Yes, full control with audit rights</td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- How We Use Your Data -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">4. How We Use Your Data</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            Data collected by the Software is used for the following purposes:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Product Improvement</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Understanding which features are used to prioritize development and improve performance, stability, and user experience.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Statistical Analysis</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Aggregated, anonymized data may be used for internal reporting and market analysis that does not identify any individual customer.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">License Compliance Verification</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Verifying that the Software is being used within the terms of the applicable license agreement.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Support and Troubleshooting</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Diagnosing and resolving technical issues reported by customers, improving error handling, and delivering targeted fixes.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Security Threat Detection</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Identifying potential security threats, abuse patterns, or unauthorized use of the Software to protect the integrity of the platform.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Website Data -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">5. Website Data</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">
            The donjonsec.com website is designed with minimal data footprint:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span>No third-party analytics or tracking scripts are used.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span>No cookies are set. The site is a static site hosted on Cloudflare Pages.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span>No personal information is collected through the Website.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span>All fonts are self-hosted. No requests are made to Google Fonts or other third-party font services.</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <span>Cloudflare, as our hosting provider, may collect standard web server logs (IP address, user-agent, request timestamps) in accordance with their own privacy policy.</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Third-Party Services -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">6. Third-Party Services</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Our Website and infrastructure rely on <strong class="font-medium text-slate-200">Cloudflare</strong> for hosting, CDN, and DNS services. Cloudflare may process data in accordance with their own privacy policy, available at
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors" rel="noopener noreferrer">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a>.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We do not use any other third-party services that collect or process user data on our Website or within the Software.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Retention -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">7. Data Retention</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Telemetry data is retained for a maximum of twelve (12) months from the date of collection, after which it is permanently deleted. License activation records are retained for the duration of the subscription term plus one (1) year.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Customers may request deletion of their data at any time by contacting
            <a href="mailto:legal@donjonsec.com" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">legal@donjonsec.com</a>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Data Security -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">8. Data Security</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            All telemetry data is transmitted over encrypted channels (TLS 1.2+). Data at rest is stored using industry-standard encryption. Access to customer data is restricted to authorized DonjonSec personnel on a need-to-know basis.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Your Rights -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">9. Your Rights</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            You may exercise the following rights regarding your data by emailing
            <a href="mailto:legal@donjonsec.com" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">legal@donjonsec.com</a>:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Access</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Request a copy of the data we hold about you.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Deletion</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Request that we delete your data, subject to legal obligations and legitimate business interests.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-300">
              <span class="mt-1.5 inline-block h-2 w-2 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-cyan-400" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              <div>
                <span class="font-medium text-slate-200">Portability</span>
                <span class="text-slate-400"> &mdash; Request your data in a structured, commonly used, machine-readable format.</span>
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We will respond to all data rights requests within thirty (30) days of receipt.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Third-Party Sharing -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">10. Third-Party Sharing</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            DonjonSec does not sell, rent, or share customer data with third parties, except as required by law or valid legal process. If we are compelled to disclose data, we will make reasonable efforts to notify the affected customer unless legally prohibited from doing so.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Children's Privacy -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">11. Children's Privacy</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            The Software and Website are not directed at children under the age of sixteen (16). We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected data from a child under 16, we will take steps to delete such data promptly.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- International Data Transfers -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">12. International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Data collected by the Software may be processed in the United States. By using the Software, you consent to the transfer of your data to the United States and acknowledge that data protection laws in the United States may differ from those in your jurisdiction.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Changes to This Policy -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            DonjonSec may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Material changes will be communicated at least thirty (30) days in advance via email or in-app notification. The updated policy will also be published at
            <a href="/legal/privacy/" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">donjonsec.com/legal/privacy</a>.
            Continued use of the Software after notification of changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Contact -->
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">14. Contact</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            For questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact:
          </p>
          <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-navy-700 bg-navy-950 p-6">
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              <span class="font-medium text-white">DonjonSec &mdash; Privacy Inquiries</span>
            </p>
            <p class="mt-2 text-slate-400">
              General:
              <a href="mailto:info@donjonsec.com" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">info@donjonsec.com</a>
            </p>
            <p class="mt-1 text-slate-400">
              Legal and data requests:
              <a href="mailto:legal@donjonsec.com" class="text-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-300 transition-colors">legal@donjonsec.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 flex justify-center">
        <a
          href="/contact/"
          class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md border border-navy-600 bg-navy-800 px-6 py-3 text-base font-semibold text-slate-200 hover:bg-navy-700 transition-colors"
        >
          Questions? Contact Us
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
